From: quark <quark@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] win32u: guard scroll info pointer before field access

get_scroll_info_ptr can return a pointer derived from an
uninitialized pScroll field in the WND structure. When pScroll
is garbage (non-zero but invalid), &pScroll->horz produces a
near-NULL pointer. Subsequent field access at offset 0x18
(curVal) causes a page fault.

Add explicit validation that the returned pointer is in a
reasonable address range before dereferencing.

Signed-off-by: quark <quark@localhost>
---
diff --git a/dlls/win32u/scroll.c b/dlls/win32u/scroll.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/dlls/win32u/scroll.c
+++ b/dlls/win32u/scroll.c
@@ -870,7 +870,7 @@ BOOL get_scroll_info( HWND hwnd, int bar, SCROLLINFO *info )
     struct scroll_info *scroll;
 
     /* handle invalid data structure */
-    if (!validate_scroll_info( info ) || !(scroll = get_scroll_info_ptr( hwnd, bar, FALSE )))
+    if (!validate_scroll_info( info ) || !(scroll = get_scroll_info_ptr( hwnd, bar, FALSE )) || (ULONG_PTR)scroll < 0x10000)
         return FALSE;
 
     /* fill in the desired scroll info structure */
